Fascinating article, I&#39;ve been extremely intrigued by Wikileaks as it has some extremely worthwhile material and I think it does offer one of the only proper challenges to the secretism and restrictive nature of most organisations and governments attitudes towards information. 

I&#39;m extremely impressed by both the editorial team&#39;s response to Mr Assange, and the work that he himself does - I jsut want to say that I didn&#39;t particularly feel this article painted Wikileaks in a bad light, just pointed out its own fairly clandestine nature and some of the reasons for it.
